  "chapter": {
    "number": 19,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Job: My Redeemer Lives"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Then Job answered:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“How long will you torment me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and crush me with your words?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ten times now you have reproached me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you shamelessly mistreat me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Even if I have truly gone astray,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "my error concerns me alone.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If indeed you would exalt yourselves above me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and use my disgrace against me,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "then understand that it is God who has wronged me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and drawn His net around me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though I cry out, ‘Violence!’ I get no response;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "though I call for help, there is no justice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has blocked my way so I cannot pass;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He has veiled my paths with darkness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has stripped me of my honor",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and removed the crown from my head.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He tears me down on every side until I am gone;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He uproots my hope like a tree.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His anger burns against me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He counts me among His enemies.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His troops advance together;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they construct a ramp against me",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and encamp around my tent.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has removed my brothers from me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "my acquaintances have abandoned me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My kinsmen have failed me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my friends have forgotten me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My guests and maidservants count me as a stranger;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I am a foreigner in their sight.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I call for my servant, but he does not answer,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "though I implore him with my own mouth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My breath is repulsive to my wife,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I am loathsome to my own family.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Even little boys scorn me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when I appear, they deride me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All my best friends despise me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and those I love have turned against me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My skin and flesh cling to my bones;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have escaped by the skin of my teeth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Have pity on me, my friends, have pity,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for the hand of God has struck me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why do you persecute me as God does?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Will you never get enough of my flesh?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I wish that my words were recorded",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and inscribed in a book,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "by an iron stylus on lead,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or chiseled in stone forever.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But I know that my Redeemer",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3171
          },
          {
            "text": "lives,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and in the end He will stand upon the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3172
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Even after my skin has been destroyed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yet in my flesh",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3173
          },
          {
            "text": "I will see God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will see Him for myself;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "my eyes will behold Him, and not as a stranger.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "How my heart yearns",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3174
          },
          {
            "text": "within me!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If you say, ‘Let us persecute him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "since the root of the matter lies with him,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3175
          },
          {
            "text": "’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "then you should fear the sword yourselves,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because wrath brings punishment by the sword,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so that you may know there is a judgment.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
